The paper deals with lossless compression of binary trees, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The use of tree straight-line programs and grammar-based compression suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.CC). The paper also discusses universal codes for structured tree sources, which could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI) or machine learning (cs.LG).
